text: This is a great place to spend time, offering a convenient and comfortable experience.  It's well-equipped with all the necessary amenities, making it a truly enjoyable location.  Everything was clean and well-maintained, and the overall atmosphere was pleasant and relaxing.

Come here to get your fresh vegetables, meats, seafood from the three (one operated by Chinese and another two by Indians) mini wet markets as well as Sheng Siong Supermarket.

You can also buy really nice Malay food like Mee Siam, Nasi Lemak and Curry Puffs from one of the mini wet markets.

There are also two coffee shops selling delicious roti prata as well as nasi lemak.

There is also a very popular remittance and money changer at the end of the street facing the end of Tampines Bus Interchange.
Good place to have a visit.
